NRSV "descendants" | RSV NIV "the people", connecting הַבָּנִים in 2:4 to בְּנֵי יִשְׁרָאֵל in 2:3.

The exact meaning of בֵּן in this verse has been much discussed. Interpretation has to take into account the suggestion in BHS apparatus that the second line of this verse, which contains the word, may be a redactional addition from v.18 (where the same phrase occurs again) and should be deleted (cf. RSV NRSV REB). If it is maintained as part of the verse, then v.18 helps in getting the meaning of the word here, since there it is paralleled by אִישׁ יְמִינֶךָ "the man of Your right" and by בֶּן־אָדָם "son of man". Most modern interpreters understand that these three expressions apply to the king, the "son" of God, the one at His right hand, perhaps an archetypical "son of man" (with messianic connotations?).

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: = direct or indirect human offspring, either male or indeterminate, either biologically or through adoption
= direct offspring of animals, either male or indeterminate
= member of a larger group of related people or objects, ◄ referred to as a child of that larger group

literally: children of a town, region, nation; hence: = people, animals, or products that are inhabitants of or originating from a place, town, region, or nation, ◄ as if they were the offspring of that place
= state in which humans and animals have a certain age, ◄ referred to as a child of a certain number of years
= state of being associated with a certain time of day, ◄ referred to as a child of that time
= state of being associated with a certain attribute, attitude, or behavior, ◄ referred to as a child of that attribute, attitude, or behavior
= title used by a male person to address someone else whom he considers superior to himself, ◄ as if he were that person's child
= title used to address a person (male if in singular) who is regarded with some degree of affection, ◄ as if he were the speaker's child
